y and carried out research into meteorology and colour blindness.","long":"The scientist John Dalton was born in North England in 1766. Although he came from a relatively poor Quaker family, he managed to become one of the most celebrated scientists of his age. Through his work, he helped to establish Manchester as a place where not only products were made but ideas were born. His reputation during his lifetime was so high that unusually a statue was erected to him before he died. Among his interests were meteorology, gasses and colour blindness. However, he is most remembered today for his pioneering thinking in the field of atomic theory. \n\nWith: \n\nJim Bennett\nFormer Director of the Museum of the History of Science at the University of Oxford and Keeper Emeritus at the Science Museum\n\nAileen Fyfe\nReader in British History at the University of St Andrews\n\nJames Sumner\nLecturer in the History of Technology at the Centre for the History of Science, Technology and Medicine at the University of Manchester\n\nProducer: Victoria Brignell."},"image_url":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/{recipe}/p04cln6b.jpg","duration":{"value":2740,"label":"45 mins"},"progress":null,"availability":{"from":"2016-10-27T10:16:37Z","to":null,"label":"Available for over a year"},"container":{"type":"brand","id":"b006qykl","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:brand:b006qykl","title":"In Our Time","synopses":{"short":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas, people and events that have shaped our world.","medium":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas, people and events that have shaped our world.","long":null},"activities":[]},"uris":[{"type":"latest","id":null,"label":"Latest","uri":"/v2/programmes/playable?container=b006qykl&sort=sequential&type=episode&experience=domestic"}],"activities":[],"play_context":null,"guidance":{"competition_warning":false,"warnings":null},"recommendation":null},{"id":"p04f14nh","type":"playable_item","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:episode:b080wbrq","network":{"id":"bbc