 Studies at the University of St Andrews\n\nand \n\nGordon Noble\nReader in Archaeology at the University of Aberdeen\n\nProducer: Simon Tillotson."},"image_url":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/{recipe}/p05ltmgf.jpg","duration":{"value":3405,"label":"56 mins"},"progress":null,"availability":{"from":"2017-11-09T12:38:33Z","to":null,"label":"Available for over a year"},"container":{"type":"brand","id":"b006qykl","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:brand:b006qykl","title":"In Our Time","synopses":{"short":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas, people and events that have shaped our world.","medium":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas, people and events that have shaped our world.","long":null},"activities":[]},"uris":[{"type":"latest","id":null,"label":"Latest","uri":"/v2/programmes/playable?container=b006qykl&sort=sequential&type=episode&experience=domestic"}],"activities":[],"play_context":null,"guidance":{"competition_warning":false,"warnings":null},"recommendation":null},{"id":"p05n7bs9","type":"playable_item","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:episode:b09drjm1","network":{"id":"bbc_radio_four","key":"radio4","short_title":"Radio 4","logo_url":"https://sounds.files.bbci.co.uk/3.5.0/networks/bbc_radio_four/{type}_{size}.{format}","network_type":"master_brand"},"release":{"date":"2017-11-16T00:00:00Z","label":"16 Nov 2017"},"titles":{"primary":"In Our Time","secondary":"Germaine de Stael","tertiary":null,"entity_title":"Germaine de Stael"},"synopses":{"short":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas and works of the great woman of letters.","medium":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas, works and life of Germaine de Stael (1766-1817), a literary critic, author, opponent of Napoleon and developer of Romanticism.","long":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the life and impact of Germaine de Staël (1766-1817) who Byron praised as Europe's greatest living writer, and was at the heart of intellectual and literary life in the France of revolution and of Napoleon. As well as attracting and inspiring others in her salon, she wrote novels, plays. literary criticism, political essays, and poems and developed the ideas behind Romanticism. She achieved this while regularly exiled from the Paris in which she was born, having fallen out with Napoleon who she opposed, becoming a towering figure in the history of European ideas.\n\nWith \n\nCatriona Seth, Marshal Foch Professor of French Literature at the University of Oxford\n\nAlison Finch, Professor Emerita of French Literature at the University of Cambridge\n\nand \n\nKatherine Astbury, Associate Professor and Reader in French Studies at the University of Warwick.\n\nProducer: Simon Tillotson."},"image_url":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/{recipe}/p05mk463.jpg","duration":{"value":2997,"label":"49 mins"},"progress":null,"availability":{"from":"2017-11-16T10:57:58Z","to":null,"label":"Available for over a year"},"container":{"type":"brand","id":"b006qykl","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:brand:b006qykl","title":"In Our Time","synopses":{"short":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas, people and events that have shaped our world.","medium":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas, people and events that have shaped our world.","long":null},"activities":[]},"uris":[{"type":"latest","id":null,"label":"Latest","uri":"/v2/programmes/playable?container=b006qykl&sort=sequential&type=episode&experience=domestic"}],"activities":[],"play_context":null,"guidance":{"competition_warning":false,"warnings":null},"recommendation":null},{"id":"p05nzf4f","type":"playable_item","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:episode:b09fj9mt","network":{"id":"bbc_radio_four","key":"radio4","short_title":"Radio 4","logo_url":"https://sounds.files.bbci.co.uk/3.5.0/networks/bbc_radio_four/{type}_{size}.{format}","network_type":"master_brand"},"release":{"date":"2017-11-23T00:00:00Z","label":"23 Nov 2017"},"titles":{"primary":"In Our Time","secondary":"Thebes","tertiary":null,"entity_title":"Thebes"},"synopses":{"short":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the Greek city of Thebes in myth, drama and history.","medium":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the myths of the ancient Greek city of Thebes, as told by Athenian dramatists, and the times when Thebes dominated Greek history.","long":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the myths and history of the ancient Greek city of Thebes and its depiction in Athenian drama. In myths it was said to be home to Heracles, Dionysus, Oedipus and Cadmus among others and, in history, was infamous for supporting Xerxes in the Persian War. Its prominence led to a struggle with the rising force of Macedon in which the Thebans were defeated at Chaironea in 338 BC, one of the most important battles in ancient history. The position of Thebes in Greek culture was enormously powerful. The strength of its myths and its proximity to Athens made it a source of stories for the Athenian theatre, and is the setting for more of the surviving plays than any other location. \n\nThe image, above, is of Oedipus answering questions of the sphinx in Thebes (cup 5th century BC).\n\n\nWith \n\nEdith Hall\nProfessor of Classics at King's College London\n\nSamuel Gartland\nLecturer in Ancient History at Corpus Christi College, University of Oxford\n\nand\n\nPaul Cartledge\nEmeritus Professor of Greek Culture and AG Leventis Senior Research Fellow at Clare College, University of Cambridge\n\n\nProducer: Simon Tillotson."},"image_url":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/{recipe}/p05nbxpq.jpg","duration":{"value":2809,"label":"46 mins"},"progress":null,"availability":{"from":"2017-11-23T12:59:20Z","to":null,"label":"Available for over a year"},"container":{"type":"brand","id":"b006qykl","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:brand:b006qykl","title":"In Our Time","synopses":{"short":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas, people and events that have shaped our world.","medium":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas, people and events that have shaped our world.","long":null},"activities":[]},"uris":[{"type":"latest","id":n