 of his supporters paid off his owner, so Douglass could be free in law and not fear recapture. After the Civil War and the abolition of slavery, he campaigned for equal rights for African-Americans, arguing against those such as Lincoln who had wanted freed slaves to leave America and found a colony elsewhere. \"We were born here,\" he said, \"and here we will remain.\"\n\nWith\n\nCeleste-Marie Bernier\nProfessor of Black Studies in the English Department at the University of Edinburgh\n\nKaren Salt\nAssistant Professor in Transnational American Studies at the University of Nottingham\n\nAnd\n\nNicholas Guyatt\nReader in North American History at the University of Cambridge\n\n\nProducer: Simon Tillotson."},"image_url":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/{recipe}/p05wrv8v.jpg","duration":{"value":3142,"label":"52 mins"},"progress":null,"availability":{"from":"2018-02-08T11:25:13Z","to":null,"label":"Available for over a year"},"container":{"type":"brand","id":"b006qykl","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:brand:b006qykl","title":"In Our Time","synopses":{"short":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas, people and events that have shaped our world.","medium":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas, people and events that have shaped our world.","long":null},"activities":[]},"uris":[{"type":"latest","id":null,"label":"Latest","uri":"/v2/programmes/playable?container=b006qykl&sort=sequential&type=episode&experience=domestic"}],"activities":[],"play_context":null,"guidance":{"competition_warning":false,"warnings":null},"recommendation":null},{"id":"p05y849q","type":"playable_item","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:episode:b09r3nwl","network":{"id":"bbc_radio_four","key":"radio4","short_title":"Radio 4","logo_url":"https://sounds.files.bbci.co.uk/3.5.0/networks/bbc_radio_four/{type}_{size}.{format}","network_type":"master_brand"},"release":{"date":"2018-02-15T00:00:00Z","label":"15 Feb 2018"},"titles":{"primary":"In Our Time","secondary":"Fungi","tertiary":null,"entity_title":"Fungi"},"synopses":{"short":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss fungi.","medium":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss fungi, organisms that play a crucial role in the earth's ecosystems.","long":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss fungi. These organisms are not plants or animals but a kingdom of their own. Millions of species of fungi live on the Earth and they play a crucial role in ecosystems, enabling plants to obtain nutrients and causing material to decay. Without fungi, life as we know it simply would not exist. They are also a significant part of our daily life, making possible the production of bread, wine and certain antibiotics. Although fungi brought about the colonisation of the planet by plants about 450 million years ago, some species can kill humans and devastate trees. \n\nWith:\n\nLynne Boddy\nProfessor of Fungal Ecology at Cardiff University\n\nSarah Gurr\nProfessor of Food Security in the Biosciences Department at the University of Exeter\n\nDavid Johnson\nN8 Chair in Microbial Ecology at the University of Manchester\n\nProducer: Victoria Brignell."},"image_url":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/{recipe}/p05xjfnx.jpg","duration":{"value":2917,"label":"48 mins"},"progress":null,"availability":{"from":"2018-02-15T11:17:03Z","to":null,"label":"Available for over a year"},"container":{"type":"brand","id":"b006qykl","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:brand:b006qykl","title":"In Our Time","synopses":{"short":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas, people and events that have shaped our world.","medium":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas, people and events that have shaped our world.","long":null},"activities":[]},"uris":[{"type":"latest","id":null,"label":"Latest","uri":"/v2/programmes/playable?container=b006qykl&sort=sequential&type=episode&experience=domestic"}],"activities":[],"play_context":null,"guidance":{"competition_warning":false,"warnings":null},"recommendation":null},{"id":"p05z0ltc","type":"playable_item","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:episode:b09rzm9y","network":{"id":"bbc_