d around the world. \n\nwith \n\nDr Michael Bailey\nRailway historian and editor of the most recent biography of Robert Stephenson\n\nJulia Elton\nPast President of the Newcomen Society for the History of Engineering and Technology\n\nand\n\nColin Divall\nProfessor Emeritus of Railway Studies at the University of York\n\nProducer: Simon Tillotson.\nThis programme is a repeat"},"image_url":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/{recipe}/p063chl2.jpg","duration":{"value":3025,"label":"50 mins"},"progress":null,"availability":{"from":"2022-01-13T01:06:07Z","to":null,"label":"Available for over a year"},"container":{"type":"brand","id":"b006qykl","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:brand:b006qykl","title":"In Our Time","synopses":{"short":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas, people and events that have shaped our world.","medium":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas, people and events that have shaped our world.","long":null},"activities":[]},"uris":[{"type":"latest","id":null,"label":"Latest","uri":"/v2/programmes/playable?container=b006qykl&sort=sequential&type=episode&experience=domestic"}],"activities":[],"play_context":null,"guidance":{"competition_warning":false,"warnings":null},"recommendation":null},{"id":"p09q0cx8","type":"playable_item","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:episode:b09z1dd7","network":{"id":"bbc_radio_four","key":"radio4","short_title":"Radio 4","logo_url":"https://sounds.files.bbci.co.uk/3.5.0/networks/bbc_radio_four/{type}_{size}.{format}","network_type":"master_brand"},"release":{"date":"2018-04-19T00:00:00Z","label":"19 Apr 2018"},"titles":{"primary":"In Our Time","secondary":"Middlemarch","tertiary":null,"entity_title":"Middlemarch"},"synopses":{"short":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss George Eliot's greatest novel, published 1871-72.","medium":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss George Eliot's Study of Provincial Life, set before the Reform Act 1832 in a small, fictional town in the Midlands surrounded by farmland.","long":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss what Virginia Woolf called 'one of the few English novels written for grown-up people'. It was written by George Eliot, the pen name of Mary Anne Evans (1819-80), published in 8 parts in 1871-72, and was originally two separate stories which became woven together. One, 'Middlemarch', focused on a doctor, Tertius Lydgate and the other, 'Miss Brooke', on Dorothea Brooke who became the central figure in the finished work. The events are set in a small town in the Midlands, surrounded by farmland, leading up to the Reform Act 1832, and the novel explores the potential to change in matters of religion, social status, marriage and politics, and is particularly concerned with the opportunities available to women to lead fulfilling lives. \n\nThe image above shows Rufus Sewell and Juliet Aubrey in the BBC adaptation, from 1994\n\nWith \n\nRosemary Ashton\nEmeritus Quain Professor of English Language and Literature at University College London\n\nKathryn Hughes\nProfessor of Life Writing at the University of East Anglia\n\nAnd \n\nJohn Bowen\nProfessor of Nineteenth-Century Literature at the University of York\n\nProducer: Simon Tillotson."},"image_url":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/{recipe}/p064gm9j.jpg","duration":{"value":3109,"label":"51 mins"},"progress":null,"availability":{"from":"2022-01-13T00:26:12Z","to":null,"label":"Available for over a year"},"container":{"type":"brand","id":"b006qykl","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:brand:b006qykl","title":"In Our Time","synopses":{"short":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas, people and events that have shaped our world.","medium":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas, people and events that have shaped our world.","long":null},"activities":[]},"uris":[{"type":"latest","id":null,"label":"Latest","uri":"/v2/programmes/playable?container=b006qykl&sort=sequential&type=episode&experience=domestic"}],"activities":[],"play_context":null,"guidance":{"competition_warning":false,"warnings":null},"recommendation":null},{"id":"p09q0dgs",