 at the University of Cambridge and Fellow of St John’s College\n\nWilliam Fitzgerald\nProfessor of Latin Language and Literature at King’s College London\n\nand \n\nEllen O’Gorman\nSenior Lecturer in Classics at the University of Bristol\n\nProducer: Simon Tillotson"},"image_url":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/{recipe}/p06q639w.jpg","duration":{"value":2937,"label":"48 mins"},"progress":null,"availability":{"from":"2022-01-13T00:21:37Z","to":null,"label":"Available for over a year"},"container":{"type":"brand","id":"b006qykl","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:brand:b006qykl","title":"In Our Time","synopses":{"short":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas, people and events that have shaped our world.","medium":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas, people and events that have shaped our world.","long":null},"activities":[]},"uris":[{"type":"latest","id":null,"label":"Latest","uri":"/v2/programmes/playable?container=b006qykl&sort=sequential&type=episode&experience=domestic"}],"activities":[],"play_context":null,"guidance":{"competition_warning":false,"warnings":null},"recommendation":null},{"id":"p09q176k","type":"playable_item","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:episode:m00017vl","network":{"id":"bbc_radio_four","key":"radio4","short_title":"Radio 4","logo_url":"https://sounds.files.bbci.co.uk/3.5.0/networks/bbc_radio_four/{type}_{size}.{format}","network_type":"master_brand"},"release":{"date":"2018-11-22T00:00:00Z","label":"22 Nov 2018"},"titles":{"primary":"In Our Time","secondary":"Hope","tertiary":null,"entity_title":"Hope"},"synopses":{"short":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the philosophy of hope - a weakness or a strength?","medium":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the development of ideas about hope, left in Pandora's box either as a consolation or as another evil, later the companion of faith and love","long":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the philosophy of hope. To the ancient Greeks, hope was closer to self-deception, one of the evils left in Pandora's box or jar, in Hesiod's story.  In Christian tradition, hope became one of the theological virtues, the desire for divine union and the expectation of receiving it, an action of the will rather than the intellect.  To Kant, 'what may I hope' was one of the three basic questions which human reason asks, while Nietzsche echoed Hesiod, arguing that leaving hope in the box was a deception by the gods, reflecting human inability to face the demands of existence. Yet even those critical of hope, like Camus, conceded that life was nearly impossible without it.\n\nWith\n\nBeatrice Han-Pile\nProfessor of Philosophy at the University of Essex\n\nRobert Stern\nProfessor of Philosophy at the University of Sheffield\n\nAnd\n\nJudith Wolfe\nProfessor of Philosophical Theology at the University of St Andrews\n\nProducer: Simon Tillotson"},"image_url":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/{recipe}/p06qv51r.jpg","duration":{"value":3181,"label":"53 mins"},"progress":null,"availability":{"from":"2022-01-13T00:38:33Z","to":null,"label":"Available for over a year"},"container":{"type":"brand","id":"b006qykl","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:brand:b006qykl","title":"In Our Time","synopses":{"short":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas, people and events that have shaped our world.","medium":"Melvyn Bragg and guests discuss the ideas, people and events that have shaped our world.","long":null},"activities":[]},"uris":[{"type":"latest","id":null,"label":"Latest","uri":"/v2/programmes/playable?container=b006qykl&sort=sequential&type=episode&experience=domestic"}],"activities":[],"play_context":null,"guidance":{"competition_warning":false,"warnings":null},"recommendation":null}],"state":"ok","style":null,"uris":null,"total":99}]},"locales":{"cy":"Cymraeg","ga":"Gaeilge","gd":"Gàidhlig"},"footerLinks":{"https://bbc.co.uk/sounds/help":"BBC Sounds Help","https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/articles/0c6dcea5-420b-4caf-b3b9-e97b605a50fd":"Contacts, Privacy and Information","https://www.bbc.co.uk/usingthebbc/account/